// ticket #11's Windows build (release.yml's build-windows job): bundles
// libmpv-2.dll (extracted by that job to ../mpv-dev/ relative to src-tauri/)
// into the installer via Tauri's resources mechanism. Unverified -- Tauri's
// own docs flag inconsistent cross-platform behavior for relative-path
// resource sources (tauri-apps/tauri#15342), and libmpv-2.dll needs to land
// wherever Windows' DLL search order actually finds it at runtime (normally
// the same directory as the .exe) for the app to even start. If this turns
// out wrong once actually run: copy the dll into src-tauri/ directly instead
// of reaching up with `../`, or fall back to `externalBin` (sidecar) instead
// of `resources`.
//
// `targets: ["nsis"]` -- confirmed the hard way (first real `tauri build`
// run on windows-latest): WiX/MSI requires a purely numeric pre-release
// identifier ("optional pre-release identifier in app version must be
// numeric-only ... for msi target"), which `2.0.0-pre.1` (this repo's
// prerelease channel, see .releaserc.json/release.yml) isn't. NSIS has no
// such restriction. Drop this override (back to the root config's
// `targets: "all"`) once releases go back to stable, non-prerelease
// versions.
{
  $schema: "https://schema.tauri.app/config/2",
  bundle: {
    targets: ["nsis"],
    resources: {
      "../mpv-dev/libmpv-2.dll": "",
    },
  },
}
